  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BUNERELA_VYIZIGIRO_End of MTC HIV Transmission in South&amp;North Health District of Bujumbura City</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Capacity building for staff and AoC and Health staff
- CHW carry out home visits and monitoring PMTCT protocole, awareness raising around HIV. 
- Sensitize men on HIV and PMTCT 
- Positive masculinities promoted by RLs
- AoC undertakes local campaigns on stigma reduction and HIV testing. 
- Support advocacy on rights of PLHIV 
- CHWs will trace positive mothers reduce loss-to-follow-up during PMTCT protocole
- Training of members of committees of IGA on the basics in micro business management per a local consultat
- IGA to increase income for vulnerable families</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increase the use of HIV services
Reduction on new born infected by HIV
Improve econmic empowerment for PLHIV
Reduce stigma and discrimination around HIV</narrative>
  </description>
